<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter id="details.aqbanking">
<chapterinfo>
  <authorgroup>
    <author> &Ralf.Habacker; &Ralf.Habacker.mail; </author>
  </authorgroup>
  <date>2025-04-25</date>
  <releaseinfo>5.2.0</releaseinfo>
</chapterinfo>

<title>Online banking</title>

<para>
  Online banking is configured by selecting the menu entry Settings
  -&gt; Configure Aqbanking,
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
  <screeninfo>KMyMoney configuration menu</screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata fileref="config_menu.png" format="PNG" />
    </imageobject>
    <textobject>
      <phrase>KMyMoney configuration menu</phrase>
    </textobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
  This menu item is visible after the associated KBanking plugin has
  been activated, which can be done via the &quot;Configure KMyMoney&quot;
  menu item and after selecting the &quot;Module&quot; entry in the left
  pane.
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
  <screeninfo>KMyMoney configuration menu</screeninfo>
  <screeninfo>png</screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata fileref="configure_plugins.png" />
    </imageobject>
    <textobject>
      <phrase>KMyMoney configuration menu</phrase>
    </textobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
  After you pressed the menu entry you will see the following dialog:
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
  <screeninfo>kbanking-wizard-page1-de.png</screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-wizard-page1.png" width="400px" />
    </imageobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<sect1 id="add_user">
  <title>Add user</title>
  <para>
    After pressing &quot;Benutzer anlegen&quot; you will be redirected
    to the &quot;Add user&quot; dialog shown below:
  </para>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-page1-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-page1.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="select_online_banking_protocol">
  <title>Select online banking protocol</title>
  <para>
    After pressing &quot;Next&quot; you will see a list of available
    online banking protocols:
  </para>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-page2-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-page2.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="configuring_a_hbci_account">
  <title>Configuring a HBCI account</title>
  <para>
    After choosing &quot;HBCI&quot; and pressing &quot;Next&quot; you
    will see the following page, on which you can select the security
    type:
  </para>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page1-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page1.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
  <para>
    See
    <ulink url="https://www.aquamaniac.de/rdm/projects/aqbanking/wiki/AqBanking6_Bankentabelle#section-2">AqBanking6
    Bank Table</ulink> for some details on the types of security
    supported by banks. If your bank is not listed there, you should
    try Pin/TAN first.
  </para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="setup_pintan">
  <title>Setup pin/Tan</title>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page2-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page2.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="select_bank_and_server_url">
  <title>Select bank and server url</title>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page3-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page3.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
  <para>
    At
    <ulink url="https://www.aquamaniac.de/rdm/projects/aqbanking/wiki/AqBanking6_Bankentabelle">AqBanking6
    Bankentabelle</ulink> you can find a list of bank server url known
    to work.
  </para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="select_bank_account_and_user_name">
  <title>Select bank account and user name</title>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page4-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page4.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="choose_extended_settings_or_continue">
  <title>Choose extended settings or continue</title>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page5-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page5.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="select_extended_settings">
  <title>Select extended settings</title>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page6-de.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page6.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="finish_creating_user">
  <title>Finish creating user</title>
  <para>
    After pressing &quot;Next&quot; aqbanking will contact the server
    and fetches the server certificate and bank info.
  </para>
  <screenshot>
    <screeninfo>kbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page7.png</screeninfo>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="aqbanking-user-wizard-hbci-page7.png" width="400px" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </screenshot>
  <para>
    If that doesn't work, you are probably affected by
    <ulink url="https://www.aquamaniac.de/rdm/issues/273">bug
    273</ulink> and need to create the account on the command line
    using the aqbanking command line tools as documented at
    <ulink url="https://www.aquamaniac.de/rdm/projects/aqbanking/wiki/SetupPinTan">Setup
    HBCI with Pin/Tan</ulink>.
  </para>
  <para>
    Otherwise, after pressing &quot;Close&quot; your user account has
    been created.
  </para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="add_account">
  <title>Add account</title>
  <para>
    In case that adding a user account did not fail, the accounts
    associated to the given bank should already be present in the
    account list.
  </para>
</sect1>
</chapter>
